				<wikidot:authorName>Weryllium</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2727655</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'd assume they ran like <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/nacho-business">200 tests</a> on that hat before they let him keep it. In-universe I figure this sort of thing is shoved into supplemental files; there's a 100-page report in a filing cabinet with photographs of every coin, their metallic composition, and the date and location they were minted.</p> <p>There's a tricky balance to strike between realistic and entertaining when it comes to how much goes into the SCP file, is basically what I'm getting at.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
