				<pubDate>Wed, 06 Feb 2019 07:18:14 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Weryllium</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2727655</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It's pretty rare that someone tells me there's <em>too much</em> going on in my skip rather than <em>too little</em> :P</p> <blockquote> <p>without too much difficulty</p> </blockquote> <p>I have to disagree, because my impatient self stared blankly at the completed &quot;infohazard craving&quot; half for at least a good week before coming up with the ending and adding it in but whatever, it's done, it's posted, it's above deletion, I'm not messing with it.</p> <p>In any case, I'm glad you found it enjoyable. Had not seen that Onion article, love it.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10188008#post-4143471</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10188008/scp-3689#post-4143471</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 06 Feb 2019 06:46:32 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ModernMajorGeneral</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>274283</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm not sure if the two core concepts here (an infohazardous sandwich craving / a sandwich that teleports you to fight a Kraken to get an ingredient) benefit that much from being mashed together in the same article. You could probably make them into two separate articles of equal or better quality without too much difficulty.</p> <p>That said, this was still enjoyable, reminds me of Long John Silver's <a href="https://www.theonion.com/long-john-silver-s-introduces-new-golden-fried-abominat-1819578026">fried abomination</a>. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
